						<p>As far as I ever witnessed it, the anxiety &amp; guilt combo seemed to me always simply the mark of overwhelming insecurity - not sure how or why it has anything to do with "female" (unless, I suppose, the term female is defined along the lines of either that which reacts with anxiety &amp; guilt or otherwise that which has the capacity to survive being overwhelmed).</p>
<p>The approach to plug the "insecurity" part of it by removing essentially experience (and even the very possibility of direct experience) is flawed of course in that the trouble is always at the "overwhelmed" threshold that simply gets lowered as a result but I still fail to see in there anything female as such - children are easily overwhelmed by quite simple situations and remain overwhelmed by them for as long as they don't develop an actual understanding of what is happening and how it works, regardless otherwise of how their biological age and sex and anything else develops on its pre-set way.</p>
